Package: wikilite
Title: Retrieve, Parse, and Analyse Wikipedia Article History and Citations
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Jonathan",
           family = "Sobel",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "jsobel83@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5111-4070"))
Description: A toolkit for mining Wikipedia article revision history and
    citations via the public MediaWiki API. Retrieves full revision
    histories and structured metadata, extracts and counts citations
    (DOIs, ISBNs, PMIDs, URLs, and Citation Style 1 templates), annotates
    DOIs through 'europepmc' and 'rcrossref', computes scientific-source
    quality metrics (SciScore), identifies revert-based edit trends across
    all Wikipedia articles, and provides visualisations including interactive
    timelines and citation networks.
